N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 10.3 - Coercive tactics to require loading and unloading services prohibited

State Regulations

No person shall, directly or indirectly, by the use of force, threats, intimidation or other coercive tactics require or attempt to require
the utilization of his or any other person's services to perform the loading or
unloading services specified in section
10.1
